DESCRIPTION:Help NC Families for Safe Streets advocate for Intelligent Spee
 d Assist technology that would reduce deaths caused by "super speeders".<br
 ><br>Attendees Arrive by 9:30 am<br>Press Conference Begins  - 10 am<br>We 
 will hold a press conference featuring the stories FSS members\, coalition 
 partners\, and community leaders urging the need for this legislation.<br>I
 SA Tech Demonstration - TBD There will be a live demonstration of the intel
 ligent speed assistance technology. Legislators\, the press\, legislative s
 taff\, and others will be able to test drive a vehicle equipped with ISA.<b
 r>Lobby Visits - TBDThroughout the day\, participants will meet directly wi
 th elected officials—both before and after the press event—to urge passage 
 of a Stop Super Speeders bill that will protect all North Carolinians. Thes
 e meetings are a powerful opportunity to share stories\, present data\, and
  make clear that safer streets are a priority across our communities. Want 
 to share your story or lobby? Register <a href="https://secure.everyaction.
 com/vFvg9xltZ0mQ2ps7dithAw2" target="_blank">here</a>.<b><br></b><br><b>Reg
 istration required?</b> <a href="https://secure.everyaction.com/vFvg9xltZ0m
 Q2ps7dithAw2" target="_blank">Yes</a> (for lobbying/speaking)<br><b>Passpor
 t eligible?</b> No<br><b>Community partner:</b> NC Families for Safe Street
 s
LAST-MODIFIED:20260415T025052Z
LOCATION:North Carolina State Capitol\, 1 E Edenton St\, Raleigh\, NC 27601
 \, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Stop Super Speeders Lobby Day
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
